VELOPER CHALLENGES------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ SUPPORTING THE APPLICATION IN PRODUCTION----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- DEVELOPER OFTEN CALLED TO RESOLVE PROBLEMS--------- DIFFICULT TO RECREATE PROBLEM OUTSIDE PRODUCTION--------- NEED TO BALANCE SUPPORT NEEDS WITH NEW DEVELOPMENT------------------------------------------------------------------- DDRESSING APPLICATION PERFORMANCE ISSUES---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- DETECTING PROBLEMS IS OFTEN REACTIVE AND POST-DEPLOYMENT--------- ISOLATING PERFORMANCE BOTTLENECKS CAN BE DIFFICULT--------- MANY DISTRIBUTED, COMPLEX LAYERS TO ANALYZE--------- DEVELOPERS GIVEN VAGUE INFORMATION ON PROBLEM--------- INCREASED TIME TO PROBLEM RESOLUTION--------------- IF YOU ARE A DEVELOPER, YOU PROBABLY FACE A NUMBER OF DEVELOPMENT CHALLENGES ON A DAILY BASIS. THERE'S A CONSTANT NEED TO KEEP CURRENT ON EMERGING TECHNOLOGIES, PRESSURE FROM YOUR CUSTOMERS TO DELIVER PRODUCTS AHEAD-OF-SCHEDULE, AND A DESIRE TO BUILD ROBUST AND SCALABLE ARCHITECTURES.------- DESPITE UNDERSTANDING THE IMPORTANCE OF-PERFORMANCE TO THE SUCCESS OF-ANY APPLICATION, AND-THE ATTEMPTING TO DESIGN AND ARCHITECT YOUR APPLICATION TO ENSURE THAT IT'S ROBUST AND SCALABLE, PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT IS PROBABLY MORE OF-AN AFTER-THOUGHT AND DOESN'T BECOME A CRITICAL ISSUE UNTIL PRODUCTION WHEN THE CUSTOMER EXPERIENCES A PROBLEM.------- IF YOU HAD A VERY SIMPLE APPLICATION, IT MIGHT NOT BE TOO DIFFICULT TO DIAGNOSE THE PROBLEM.- BUT- YOU'RE PROBABLY USING WEB-SERVICES, JMS, SERVLETS, EJBS, AND OTHER DISTRIBUTED TECHNOLOGIES. WHEN YOU'RE GIVEN A-SUPPORT REQUEST SUCH AS, "THE APPLICATION IS SLOW", YOU'RE MOST LIKELY SPENDING COUNTLESS HOURS TRYING TO IDENTIFY AND DIAGNOSE THE PERFORMANCE PROBLEM. YOU WON'T HAVE ENOUGH-INFORMATION TO KNOW WHERE TO EVEN START, WHICH WILL MAKE IT VERY DIFFICULT TO RECREATE THE PROBLEM OUTSIDE OF PRODUCTION.------- THIS LEADS US TO THE DEVELOPER'S DILEMMA. IF YOU WANT TO SPEND MORE TYPE PLAYING WITH NEW TECHNOLOGIES SUCH AS GRID COMPUTING OR AOP--OR YOU WANT TO BUILD MORE FUNCTIONALITY, YOU HAVE TO BALANCE THAT WITH THE REQUIREMENTS TO SUPPORT THE APPLICATION.---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- RESOLVING PERFORMANCE PROBLEMS TODAY------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- COMMON PROBLEM RESOLUTION APPROACHES---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- PRINT STATEMENTS OR LOG FILES---------- OPERATING SYSTEM UTILITIES---------- THREAD DUMPS---------- SIMPLE MANAGEMENT TOOLS---------- TRIAL AND ERROR--------------------------------------------------------------------! KEY ISSUES IN PROBLEM RESOLUTION TODAY---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- TIME TO RESOLUTION IS TOO LONG----------- DEVELOPERS REQUIRED TO DIAGNOSE PROBLEMS---------- PROBLEM MAY NOT BE CODE-RELATED---------- OFTEN REQUIRES MULTIPLE DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS--